.TH eroosterctl-user-passwd 1 "June 2026" "eroosterctl" "Erooster Manual"
.SH NAME
eroosterctl\-user\-passwd \- change a mail user's password
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B eroosterctl user passwd
\fIemail\fR
[\fI\-\-current\-password\fR \fIsecret\fR]
[\fI\-\-new\-password\fR \fIsecret\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Changes the password for an existing mail user. The current password must be
provided and verified before the new password is accepted. Prompted
interactively when stdin is a TTY and either flag is omitted.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fIemail\fR
Email address of the user (required positional argument).
.TP
\fB\-\-current\-password\fR \fIsecret\fR
The user's existing password. Prefer using the interactive prompt to avoid
the value appearing in shell history or process listings.
.TP
\fB\-\-new\-password\fR \fIsecret\fR
The replacement password. Prefer using the interactive prompt.
.SH EXAMPLES
.EX
# Guided interactive change (recommended)
eroosterctl user passwd alice@example.com

# Scripted change using secrets from environment
eroosterctl user passwd alice@example.com \
  --current-password "$OLD_PW" \
  --new-password "$NEW_PW"
.EE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
\fB0\fR
Password changed successfully.
.TP
\fB1\fR
Current password incorrect or database error.
.TP
\fB2\fR
Required flag missing in non\-interactive mode.
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBeroosterctl\-user\fR(1),
\fBeroosterctl\-user\-add\fR(1)
